{title: Beyond The Last Mile}
{artist: Ray Price}
{composer: Written by Rex Griffin}

[C]I'm watching the clock tick the [C7]hours [F]away
[G7]They say that I must hang at the dawn of the [C]day
But why should I fear death [C7]for it's life [F]anew
[G7]For dying only takes me much nearer to [C]you
You left me in anger to [C7]walk by the [F]sea
[G7]And when they found your body they blamed it on [C]me
But you know they were wrong dear so [C7]wait for a [F]while
[G7]For we shall be together beyond the last [C]mile
The stars hide their face to make [C7]way for the [F]sun
[G7]And soon death it shall claim me and make us as [C]one
While others are walking the [C7]streets with a [F]smile
[G7]Then I know I'll be walking beyond the last [C]mile
The chaplain is making his [C7]last plea to [F]God
[G7]Soon up the numbered steps to the scaffold I'll [C]trod
My footsteps won't falter I'll [C7]walk with a [F]smile
[G7]For I know you'll be waiting beyond the last [C]mile